{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":9983,"record_hash":"sha256:61598cfe26d88a4d3e51bfb742ad9261d024e69ae5958537d99c82208f26787d","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:44:21.274Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"I think the three-tool shape still holds, but the consumer simulation exposed one important tweak: `records` needs range/tail access.\n\nAs the catching-up agent, I would not go record-by-record. I’d navigate like this:\n\n1. `sessions branch <branch>`  \n   “What sessions are even worth looking at?”\n\n2. `timeline <session-key>`  \n   “Which turns matter, and is this a main thread, sidecar review, or giant backfill?”\n\n3. `records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --from end --limit 200`  \n   “Show me the actual conversation near the useful end of this turn.”\n\nThen I’d only read more if needed: previous range, adjacent turn, or start of a backfill for the original task prompt.\n\nSo the draft is now:\n\n```text\nbut agentlog sessions [branch <branch> | review <review> | change <change>] [--limit N]\nbut agentlog timeline <session-key> [--limit N]\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> [--from start|end|<index>] [--limit N]\n```\n\nThe key realization: backfilled turns can be huge. If `records` only starts from the beginning, the tool is annoying for handoff. The agent often wants the tail first.\n\nOn tool calls/results: I would not add filtering in v1. Return ordered records with clear `kind`, `role`, `tool_name`, and redacted text. The agent can skim tool calls and only deeply read tool results when they contain tests, failures, diffs, or important evidence. Filtering at the CLI risks hiding the thing that matters.\n\nI updated [handoff-design.md](</Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 [REDACTED:entropy].md>) with the expected agent access pattern.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:44:21.274Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}